div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Gwoo Shee Ah Look for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. | NO. 2647 Stipulation.

It is hereby stipulated by and between the attorneys for the Petitioner and Respondent in the above entitled cause, that the respondent may serve and file a return to the amended petition, at any time before the Court has finally decided the case, and that the respondent may put in counter affidavits as soon as he is able to secure the same, and that the return shall be considered as having been served and filed on time.
div1.ab: Jesse Frye & Wilbur & Spencer Attorney for Petitioner
Clay Allen G.P. Fishburne Attorney for Respondent.
div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington
In the Matter of the Application of Gwoo Shee Ah Look for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
2x Filed in the U.S. District Court Western Dist. of Washington APR 29 1914 Frank L. Crosby, Clerk, By EML Deputy
